The paper deals with the Art Gallery Problem, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and computational complexity theory. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses algebraic methods and perturbation analysis, which are common in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper analyzes the expected performance of algorithms, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
